oc:kn_4869d814 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When defining positioning strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "To reverse-engineer a positioning statement: 'For [target audience], [product] is the [category] that [key benefit] because [reason to believe].' Then choose category strategy: create new category, reframe existing, win existing, or niche within." ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_5665f34b a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When visualizing competitive positioning" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Plot competitors on a 2x2 positioning map using the two most market-relevant dimensions. Identify the underserved quadrant or where your differentiation is strongest. Choose from common axis pairs: Price vs Capability, Ease vs Power, SMB vs Enterprise, Point Solution vs Platform, Innovative vs Established." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A 2x2 matrix forces clarity about relative positioning and reveals whitespace opportunities" .

oc:kn_74ba868b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up ongoing competitive intelligence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Research cadence: Deep competitive analysis quarterly (all sources), competitive monitoring monthly (scan for changes), real-time alerts ongoing (brand mentions, press, job postings). Update battlecards quarterly minimum and immediately after major competitor announcements." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Competitive landscapes shift constantly; periodic deep dives supplemented by continuous monitoring catch strategic moves early" .

oc:kn_77cfa0d3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "Web search capability is required to research competitor websites, news, review sites, and social media presence." .

oc:kn_799a6c07 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When developing positioning strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never position against a competitor instead of for a customer need, claim too many differentiators (pick 1-2), use category jargon customers don't use, position on features rather than outcomes, or change positioning too frequently." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These pitfalls confuse the market, dilute differentiation, and erode credibility with buyers" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_836e1d54 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting the competitive brief output" ;
    oc:directiveContent """## Competitive Brief — {date}
### 1. Executive Summary (2-3 sentences + key opportunity/threat)
### 2. Competitor Profiles (overview, messaging, product, content, strengths, weaknesses)
### 3. Messaging Comparison Matrix
### 4. Content Gap Analysis
### 5. Opportunities
### 6. Threats
### 7. Recommended Actions (quick wins + strategic moves)""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "date" .

oc:kn_9434b1cd a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing competitor messaging" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Assess competitor messaging on 5 dimensions: Clarity (understandable in 5 seconds), Differentiation (distinct or generic), Proof (claims backed by evidence), Consistency (across channels), Resonance (addresses real pain points)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Systematic assessment prevents subjective bias and reveals specific vulnerabilities to exploit" .

oc:kn_d6a26b6e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When running a competitive brief" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Gather inputs: competitor names (required), company/product context (recommended), focus areas (optional). 2. Research each competitor via web: website messaging, recent news (6 months), content strategy, review sites, job postings. 3. Build competitor profiles: company overview, messaging analysis, product positioning, content strategy, strengths, weaknesses. 4. Create messaging comparison matrix across dimensions (tagline, buyer, differentiator, tone, value prop). 5. Perform content gap analysis: topics, formats, keywords. 6. Identify opportunities (positioning gaps, unclaimed angles, underserved segments). 7. Identify threats (competitor strengths, favorable trends, recent moves). 8. Recommend 3-5 actions: quick wins + strategic moves." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_e93159e2 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When gathering inputs and presenting output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Competitor name(s) are required input. Research recency is critical — always note the date so users know data freshness. Recent news should cover last 6 months only." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Competitive intelligence degrades rapidly; dated information leads to poor strategic decisions" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

_:ref_0f9432143fd50a17 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Topics they cover that you do not**: potential gaps in your content strategy" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_1f916f6722c0992e a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Job postings** — hiring signals that indicate strategic direction (optional)" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

